Number Sequence Finder
This program allows you to input a sequence of numbers and find the next numbers in the sequence based on a pattern. The program can detect linear, quadratic, and geometric patterns, as well as other types of patterns.

Prerequisites
To run this program, you'll need to have Python 3 installed on your computer.

Installing
Download the number_sequence.py file from the repository.
Save the file in a directory on your computer.
Running the Program
Open a command prompt or terminal window.
Navigate to the directory where the number_sequence.py file is saved.
Type python number_sequence.py to run the program.
Follow the prompts to input a sequence of numbers and find the next numbers in the sequence.
Sample Input and Output
lua
Copy code
Enter a sequence of at least four numbers, separated by spaces (or 'quit' to exit): 1 2 3 4
The next three numbers in the sequence are: 5 6 7

Enter a sequence of at least four numbers, separated by spaces (or 'quit' to exit): 1 2 4 7
No pattern can be detected.

Enter a sequence of at least four numbers, separated by spaces (or 'quit' to exit): quit
